text:


Context. I (14M) with two siblings and a mother ( F). I and my siblings switch off every Friday, and this has been the case for about a year. My parents were previously in a divorce for 2 years. Not that this justifies my maturity in this situation, but it has been rough. My mom has done things like telling my homeroom teacher to tell me lies about my father. She has taken money out of me and my sibling's college funds that my dad has been saving since I was born. My father has introduced his fiance along the way (very nice and kind) but when I was skeptical at first he said that I should adjust faster.

&amp;#x200B;

So a few days before my birthday on her week, she said that we would be having a dinner to celebrate the occasion at the local dinner place. I pleaded for her not to invite anybody randomly (like some random high school friend) because it just makes the situation more awkward, and she has done it before. She says that she wouldn't do anything like that.

&amp;#x200B;

When I and my siblings got to the restaurant that day, boom. Mom's new boyfriend. No warning to any of us, and now wanting us to meet him for the first time. Very awkwardly.

&amp;#x200B;

I was fuming. Even though my father introduced his girlfriend more carefully, this was the final straw. He then proceeded to wish me a happy birthday and he gave me a card with a $50 steam gift card in it.

&amp;#x200B;

Throughout the dinner, I was just pure anger. I remember thinking that I wanted to sock my mom in the face when I got home. I shared that thought with my brother, and he said that I was being immature and that I should handle the situation better. I did not hurt my mom but go home and play video games.

&amp;#x200B;

AITA? Am I being dramatic about this whole ordeal and everything else? A lot of people have it worse.

I am an intern in a  company where there are many sub departments. My internship is about to be over and, in spite of very good performance, they haven't offered me a job. Now, on a fine Friday evening, I see a job opening in another department where my skills are a good match. The opening has a deadline of 1 day for application and so I apply immediately, without telling my current boss. I thought I could just tell him on Monday or if I receive a positive response from the job. 

&amp;#x200B;

Now on Monday morning my boss receives a call from the other department head, asking about my situation (I wasn't there) . You could imagine how weird the conversation must have been. When I come to the office today, my boss is a bit pissed (Although he told me he recommended me to the other dept). He also told me it really hurts my chances in the getting the job at the other dept. because it appears like backstabbing. 

&amp;#x200B;

So, AITA? Also, what should I do now (And in future) ?
